WEBVTT

00:32.575 --> 00:34.827
(TENSE, PULSING BEAT)

00:36.328 --> 00:37.955
(MAN SPEAKS, CUTS OUT ABRUPTLY)

00:38.080 --> 00:40.374
(WOMAN SPEAKS,
CUTS OUT ABRUPTLY)

00:41.876 --> 00:43.836
FEMALE REPORTER: The last
decade has seen a renaissance

00:43.961 --> 00:45.796
for international terrorism.

00:45.921 --> 00:47.882
(EXPLOSION)

00:48.007 --> 00:50.718
This has been precipitated,
at least in part,

00:50.843 --> 00:54.263
by a status quo of negotiation
and concession

00:54.388 --> 00:57.516
enabling many recent terrorist
actions to be successful

00:57.641 --> 00:59.018
for their perpetrators.

00:59.143 --> 01:01.604
These successes increased
the various groups'

01:01.729 --> 01:03.272
perceived legitimacy--
(TV SHUTTING OFF)

01:04.440 --> 01:06.692
(TENSE MUSIC)

01:08.527 --> 01:10.071
(PEOPLE SHOUT, CHANT IN ARABIC)

01:10.196 --> 01:11.614
MALE REPORTER:
In overseas news,

01:11.739 --> 01:14.617
US Special Forces have
made a disastrous attempt

01:14.742 --> 01:18.579
to free 52 Americans held
captive in Iran. Casualty--

01:18.704 --> 01:20.873
(STATIC CRACKLES)

01:21.332 --> 01:23.876
(TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES)

01:25.669 --> 01:28.589
MALE REPORTER: Back at home,
exactly one year ago tomorrow,

01:28.714 --> 01:31.300
the British people voted Prime
Minister Margaret Thatcher

01:31.425 --> 01:32.510
into power.

01:32.635 --> 01:34.386
Mrs Thatcher's
unswerving commitment

01:34.512 --> 01:36.514
to economic and social reform

01:36.639 --> 01:39.809
has been controversial, and
she remains a divisive figure

01:39.934 --> 01:43.187
in a tenuous position.
On today's programme--

01:43.312 --> 01:45.106
- ...that kind of
resource is not adequate.

01:45.231 --> 01:48.192
- Though we have to leave it.
Mr Timms, thank you.

01:48.317 --> 01:49.652
- With the bank holiday
nearly here,

01:49.777 --> 01:51.529
many Londoners will be
planning to go away.

01:51.654 --> 01:52.947
But for those left in the city,

01:53.072 --> 01:55.616
there will be plenty
of diversions.

02:39.869 --> 02:41.996
(IN ARABIC):
<i>God is with us.</i>

02:50.337 --> 02:51.046
(DOOR BANGS OPEN)

02:51.172 --> 02:52.715
MAN: Get down!
Get down, or you die!

02:52.840 --> 02:55.176
(WOMAN SCREAMS,
MEN SHOUT IN ARABIC)

02:57.386 --> 02:59.555
(TENSE MUSIC GROWS)

02:59.680 --> 03:02.057
(GLASS SHATTERS, MEN SHOUT IN ARABIC)
(RAPID GUNFIRE)

03:02.183 --> 03:03.601
(SCREAMS)
- Everyone out!

03:03.726 --> 03:05.227
Out! Hurry up!

03:05.352 --> 03:06.687
Get down!

03:06.812 --> 03:08.731
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

03:09.273 --> 03:10.399
(SHOUTS)

03:13.777 --> 03:14.987
- Sam Harris, BBC.

03:15.112 --> 03:18.657
- Everyone, on your knees!
Down! Down! Down!

03:18.782 --> 03:20.868
- Do as he says.

03:20.993 --> 03:22.745
- OK. Good.

03:22.870 --> 03:24.330
Hassan.

03:27.333 --> 03:30.461
(TENSE MUSIC)

03:31.503 --> 03:33.130
- Don't be stupid,
you'll get us all killed.

03:33.255 --> 03:34.465
(FIRES GUN)
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

03:34.590 --> 03:35.925
- Don't move! Don't talk!

03:36.050 --> 03:36.884
(SOBS)

03:37.009 --> 03:40.471
You-- you want to die?

03:40.596 --> 03:42.014
I said, 'You want to die?'

03:44.475 --> 03:47.895
(GATE CLANGS SHUT,
CHAINS RATTLE)

03:49.855 --> 03:52.358
(MAN SPEAKS ARABIC)

04:05.496 --> 04:07.748
- It's definitely
the Iranian Embassy.

04:08.624 --> 04:11.752
Weren't Chris and Sim
getting visas for Iran today?

04:11.877 --> 04:13.295
MAN: Oh, bloody hell.

04:13.420 --> 04:16.798
(SIRENS WAIL, INDISTINCT
POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

04:19.218 --> 04:19.969
- No closer.

04:20.094 --> 04:22.096
- BBC. I have colleagues in there.

04:22.221 --> 04:23.430
- Yeah, back, I said.

04:23.555 --> 04:26.308
(DOOR OPENS, CHILDREN SHOUT,
MEN SHOUT)

04:26.433 --> 04:27.685
- What's going on?

04:27.810 --> 04:28.936
- Hey, you can't do that.

04:29.061 --> 04:31.605
- Free country last time
I checked, pal.

04:31.730 --> 04:34.191
(SIRENS WAIL)

04:35.067 --> 04:36.986
- No, no, no, no, no! Get back!

04:37.111 --> 04:38.320
All of you, get back!

04:38.445 --> 04:39.863
MAN: Wait, wait, wait, wait!

04:39.989 --> 04:40.990
- I'll be back.

04:41.115 --> 04:42.491
TERRORIST: Bring
negotiator now!

04:42.616 --> 04:46.245
- Shit.
- I want a negotiator here now!

04:53.252 --> 04:56.213
- Tony, you're not
going to believe this.

04:56.338 --> 04:59.216
(DOOR BURSTS OPEN,
GUNFIRE EXPLODES)

04:59.341 --> 05:01.385
(MAN) MUFFLED:
Clear! Go! Go! Go!

05:01.510 --> 05:04.054
(MAN GRUNTS LOUDLY)

05:08.392 --> 05:10.394
- That was shit.

05:10.519 --> 05:12.104
(LIGHTS CLICK ON)

05:12.229 --> 05:14.398
(BREATHES LOUDLY)

05:15.190 --> 05:16.817
(PANTS) How's that, then, Roy?

05:16.942 --> 05:18.736
- You never checked
behind the door.

05:18.861 --> 05:20.612
- Oh, fuck.
- You're dead. So is he.

05:20.738 --> 05:22.740
(PAGER BEEPS)

05:28.912 --> 05:31.540
All right, boys! Get
yourselves outside now!

05:31.665 --> 05:35.377
Outside, boys!
- Someone's pushed the wrong button.

05:35.502 --> 05:39.048
- 30 seconds! Let's go! Now!

05:39.173 --> 05:41.091
- Now, boys!

05:46.388 --> 05:47.681
- John!

05:49.224 --> 05:51.560
- What's the deal, mate? Don't
tell me it's a fucking exercise.

05:51.685 --> 05:53.520
- Nah, terrorists in London.

05:53.645 --> 05:55.773
Multiple hostages.

05:56.982 --> 05:58.192
- Huh?

05:58.317 --> 06:00.569
- We're finally fucking on.

06:00.694 --> 06:01.612
- Right, lads.

06:01.737 --> 06:03.447
We're off to London to
meet the fucking Queen!

06:03.572 --> 06:05.657
Do some shopping.

06:11.246 --> 06:13.582
(MUSIC BUILDS)

06:23.675 --> 06:25.969
(POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

06:49.785 --> 06:51.245
(WOMAN SPEAKS FARSI)

06:51.370 --> 06:53.747
(MAN SPEAKS FARSI OVER PHONE)

07:01.422 --> 07:04.550
- They say they are the
Democratic Revolutionary Front

07:04.675 --> 07:07.469
for the liberation
of Arabistan.

07:07.594 --> 07:10.055
(MAN SPEAKS FARSI OVER PHONE)

07:15.144 --> 07:20.232
- They demand the release of 91
Arabs held in prisons in Iran.

07:21.483 --> 07:24.027
(MAN SPEAKS FARSI)

07:28.907 --> 07:30.117
(LINE HANGS UP)

07:32.578 --> 07:34.788
- What is it?

07:34.913 --> 07:36.373
- Unless these demands are met,

07:36.498 --> 07:39.710
they will kill a hostage
at noon tomorrow.

07:45.632 --> 07:46.925
- Perfect timing.

07:47.050 --> 07:48.802
You know DS Tucker.

07:48.927 --> 07:49.887
- Of course.

07:50.012 --> 07:51.263
- Max.

07:51.388 --> 07:53.390
- Tom Lovett -- You'll be supporting him
on the day shift.

07:53.515 --> 07:55.851
- We were both on the
Bramshill negotiators course.

07:55.976 --> 07:57.227
- I remember.

07:57.352 --> 07:59.104
- Good. Now, time to put
theory into practice.

07:59.229 --> 08:01.315
We know they have
one of ours --

08:01.440 --> 08:04.735
a PC Trevor Lock of
the diplomatic squad.

08:04.860 --> 08:08.322
- Yeah. Armed -- Smith & Wesson
.38 revolver.

08:08.447 --> 08:10.949
Don't know if he's used
it, still got it or what.

08:11.074 --> 08:13.827
- If he's still got it, they won't expect
an English copper to be armed.

08:13.952 --> 08:16.413
- Yes. Could be a good
or a bad thing.

08:16.538 --> 08:19.041
DELLOW: Gotta
keep them talking.

08:19.166 --> 08:21.001
- Standard Army field phone.

08:21.126 --> 08:23.337
No listening devices,
so nothing to find.

08:23.462 --> 08:25.964
But we hang up here, it's off.

08:26.089 --> 08:28.675
They hang up, it stays open.
Never switches off.

08:28.800 --> 08:31.136
Which means that, well, we
can hear anything they say

08:31.261 --> 08:32.888
within range.

08:33.013 --> 08:34.890
- That's very clever.
- Yeah.

08:35.015 --> 08:37.558
- Well, let's get on
with it, shall we?

08:37.683 --> 08:39.061
- Police are settling in tonight

08:39.186 --> 08:41.104
for a long wait around
the embassy in Kensington.

08:41.230 --> 08:44.399
The embassy's in Princes Gate,
just off Kensington Road,

08:44.525 --> 08:48.779
and the area almost from the Albert Hall
to Ennismore Gardens has been sealed off.

08:48.904 --> 08:51.031
Dozens of people from
nearby houses and offices

08:51.156 --> 08:54.326
in this most fashionable part
of London have been evacuated.

08:54.451 --> 08:57.287
- I lived right through London
throughout the war,

08:57.412 --> 09:00.249
so bombing was something
that I was brought up with.

09:00.374 --> 09:02.501
- Metropolitan Police are
by now all too experienced

09:02.626 --> 09:04.878
in this kind of incident,
and well-oiled plans

09:05.003 --> 09:06.838
have sprung into action.

09:06.964 --> 09:09.216
FEMALE REPORTER: In scenes more
reminiscent of Northern Ireland

09:09.341 --> 09:13.262
or America, guns appear on
the streets of the capital.

09:13.387 --> 09:14.930
The question here, too, is

09:15.055 --> 09:19.434
do authorities face terrorism
with negotiation or force

09:19.560 --> 09:21.812
on British soil?

09:21.937 --> 09:26.149
This is Kate Adie,
live from Princes Gate.

09:26.275 --> 09:27.818
- The rest of today's
news a little later,

09:27.943 --> 09:29.861
and of course we'll be
going back to the embassy

09:29.987 --> 09:32.155
if there are any developments.

09:48.422 --> 09:49.881
- I'm starving.

09:50.007 --> 09:52.467
- Here. You'll need to be.

09:53.885 --> 09:56.179
Guess what I just heard?
- What?

09:56.305 --> 09:59.224
- The terrorists called
BBC Television Centre.

09:59.349 --> 10:00.517
- What are they demanding?

10:00.642 --> 10:02.394
- I don't know.

10:02.519 --> 10:04.813
- I guess the real question
is what will Mrs T

10:04.938 --> 10:06.815
and the Government
concede to them?

10:06.940 --> 10:10.277
- I don't know. Not these
bloody sandwiches, I hope.

10:10.986 --> 10:12.487
- You've had worse.

10:12.613 --> 10:14.698
- When?
(CHUCKLES)

10:19.161 --> 10:21.622
- No, don't get up,
gentlemen, please.

10:21.747 --> 10:23.040
- I think you know everyone.

10:23.165 --> 10:24.958
MI5, MI6.

10:25.083 --> 10:26.001
Metropolitan Police.

10:26.126 --> 10:28.629
- Colonel Rose?
- Special Air Service.

10:33.300 --> 10:35.093
- Well, I have spoken
to the Prime Minister,

10:35.218 --> 10:36.887
and she is firm --

10:37.012 --> 10:40.515
the rule of British law
must be applied here.

10:40.641 --> 10:44.186
On that she will not be swayed.

10:44.311 --> 10:49.816
So, what is the, uh,
first order of business?

10:49.941 --> 10:52.110
- Uh, to determine the
Government's bottom line

10:52.235 --> 10:53.487
on negotiations.

10:53.612 --> 10:56.657
- And under what conditions
the SAS would take over

10:56.782 --> 10:58.325
from the police.

10:58.450 --> 11:01.578
- We can't give them what they
want, I'll tell you that much.

11:01.703 --> 11:03.288
The Iranian Government
are point-blank

11:03.413 --> 11:05.290
refusing to play ball.

11:06.541 --> 11:08.710
They're not releasing
anyone from jail.

11:12.923 --> 11:17.219
- Well, are your men ready to
go in, Colonel, if need be?

11:17.344 --> 11:19.471
- An immediate assault plan
has been drawn up

11:19.596 --> 11:22.224
based on what little
intelligence we have.

11:22.349 --> 11:25.811
If it comes to it,
it won't be pretty.

11:37.698 --> 11:39.199
(MAN) INTERCOM: Fucking
press are everywhere.

11:39.324 --> 11:41.827
Do not let them make you.

11:48.083 --> 11:49.459
- All right.

11:49.584 --> 11:53.213
Just remember, lads,
we're cleaners.

11:53.338 --> 11:58.176
- Aye. Cleaners armed
to the fucking teeth.

12:48.435 --> 12:51.563
(TV PLAYS FAINTLY)

12:55.484 --> 12:57.944
Now, this is more
like it, lads.

12:59.279 --> 13:01.990
(INDISTINCT VOICES)

13:04.326 --> 13:07.162
REPORTER:...no sooner did the Iranians burst
into the Iranian embassy,

13:07.287 --> 13:09.539
police interpreter made
the first contact with them

13:09.664 --> 13:10.874
and began the delicate task of

13:10.999 --> 13:12.584
trying to get the
hostages released

13:12.709 --> 13:15.504
and find out what precisely
the raiders wanted.

13:15.629 --> 13:18.590
They are demanding the release
of 91 Arabs held in prison

13:18.715 --> 13:20.175
in south Iran.

13:20.300 --> 13:22.886
If the demands are not met,
they will blow up the hostages

13:23.011 --> 13:24.679
and themselves.

13:25.514 --> 13:26.890
Police are keeping
the Foreign Office

13:27.015 --> 13:30.352
informed of developments,
but they are in full charge.

13:30.477 --> 13:33.563
Most of the negotiations have
been conducted with one man.

13:33.688 --> 13:37.234
The police are operating with
their customary caution.

13:37.359 --> 13:39.486
Fewest possible details
of the police operation

13:39.611 --> 13:40.904
have been disclosed.

13:41.029 --> 13:43.990
RADIO: In a tense reference to the siege,
in the Commons this afternoon,

13:44.115 --> 13:47.160
the Home Secretary said, "We are in the middle
of delicate operations."

13:47.285 --> 13:48.453
WHITELAW: And of
course we assume

13:48.578 --> 13:50.205
there is a significantly
greater number

13:50.330 --> 13:54.125
of Iranian hostages,
mostly staff of the embassy.

13:54.251 --> 13:58.171
- He reiterated that police aid
the release of the hostages

13:58.296 --> 14:00.507
without bloodshed.

14:00.632 --> 14:03.426
- Iranian Government's accused
Western governments --

14:03.552 --> 14:05.595
it's the West's fault, as usual.

14:05.720 --> 14:09.933
Have you seen this?
Dear old Mail. Never fails.

14:10.058 --> 14:12.769
This, apparently, is our fault.

14:12.894 --> 14:14.729
- Watch out! BBC are here,

14:14.855 --> 14:16.690
inflaming the
situation as usual.

14:16.815 --> 14:18.066
- Piss off, Jimmy.

14:18.191 --> 14:20.026
- Yeah, piss off, Jimmy.

14:20.151 --> 14:21.653
- OK.

14:21.778 --> 14:24.364
- Let's get on with it.

14:24.489 --> 14:26.533
Nice cape.
(LAUGHS)

14:26.658 --> 14:28.451
- Thank you.

14:32.163 --> 14:33.081
(SIGHS)

14:33.206 --> 14:37.586
- Hey. Tom didn't go
home last night.

14:37.711 --> 14:39.045
- You're joking.
- No. Wish I was.

14:39.170 --> 14:42.257
Stayed here with the night shift.
He's wound tighter than a horse's arse.

14:42.382 --> 14:44.426
- Seen this? A hostage
in the embassy

14:44.551 --> 14:47.888
called the BBC's London office.
It was leaked from there.

14:48.013 --> 14:49.180
- I thought they cut everything.

14:49.306 --> 14:50.932
- Apparently there's a
phone still operating.

14:51.057 --> 14:53.685
- We can't negotiate
in the bloody press.

14:56.688 --> 14:58.481
- One hour till deadline, boys.

14:58.607 --> 15:00.483
Maggie's made it clear
anybody gets killed,

15:00.609 --> 15:02.694
she's sending us in.

15:03.653 --> 15:07.782
- Is there anything else we should know?
- No. It's a black hole.

15:07.908 --> 15:09.242
- So it's in through
the front door

15:09.367 --> 15:12.120
and hope the whole place
doesn't go "bang", then.

15:12.245 --> 15:14.581
(TENSE MUSIC)

15:16.750 --> 15:18.376
Right.

15:23.298 --> 15:25.342
(WEAPONS CLICK, RATTLE)

15:35.977 --> 15:39.105
- You all right, mate?
- Yeah.

15:42.275 --> 15:43.485
(PHONE RINGS LOUDLY)

15:43.610 --> 15:46.529
- Get him talking.
We need to buy some time.

15:46.655 --> 15:48.073
- Hello?

15:48.198 --> 15:48.990
(SPEAKS FARSI)

15:49.115 --> 15:51.660
(TERRORIST SPEAKS FARSI)

15:58.416 --> 16:01.294
- He demands the release of
his comrades in Arabistan.

16:01.419 --> 16:04.464
Your Government must
or they will take action.

16:04.589 --> 16:06.341
- Tell him our bosses are
looking at their demands,

16:06.466 --> 16:08.510
trying to contact Iran.

16:08.635 --> 16:11.012
(SPEAKS FARSI)

16:13.390 --> 16:16.267
(TERRORIST CHUCKLES,
SPEAKS FARSI)

16:17.435 --> 16:19.396
- They have already
talked to Tehran.

16:19.521 --> 16:21.606
- Tell them they have no power in
the situation. They're trapped.

16:21.731 --> 16:23.733
(SPEAKS FARSI)

16:26.194 --> 16:30.532
(CONVERSATION BETWEEN TERRORIST
AND INTERPRETER PLAYS)

16:38.707 --> 16:43.128
(TERRORIST AND INTERPRETER
ARGUE IN FARSI)

16:43.253 --> 16:44.462
(SHOUTS IN FARSI)

16:44.587 --> 16:46.673
(LINE HANGS UP)

16:47.465 --> 16:48.258
- Don't they understand?

16:48.383 --> 16:49.509
- Tom...

16:56.474 --> 16:58.810
What did the Iranians
say to them?

17:01.354 --> 17:03.940
- They welcome all the
hostages to be martyrs

17:04.065 --> 17:06.984
for the great
Islamic State of Iran.

17:09.945 --> 17:13.241
(TERRORIST SPEAKS FARSI)

17:13.366 --> 17:15.617
- This is Sunray. Stand to.

17:15.743 --> 17:18.538
15 minutes till deadline.
Stand to.

17:18.663 --> 17:20.498
- We're on, boys.

17:20.623 --> 17:21.958
- Let's fucking have it.

17:22.083 --> 17:23.710
(GUNS CLICK)

18:03.541 --> 18:06.336
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

18:30.819 --> 18:32.320
- Max...

18:33.029 --> 18:36.449
the Army's next door,
champing at the bit to get in.

18:36.574 --> 18:40.495
I think the boss
said it's the SAS.

18:40.620 --> 18:44.040
- You serious?

18:44.165 --> 18:45.834
(SIGHS)
That's all we need.

18:45.959 --> 18:50.046
- Word from upstairs is if
someone's shot, they go in.

18:52.590 --> 18:54.884
- We'd better make sure no one is.

19:06.187 --> 19:08.773
(RECEIVER CLICKS, LINE RINGS)

19:10.400 --> 19:12.527
(SILENCE)

19:12.652 --> 19:16.322
(RECEIVER CLICKS, LINE RINGS)

19:18.324 --> 19:22.620
(INDISTINCT FARSI
CONVERSATIONS)

19:22.745 --> 19:24.289
- Hello?

19:24.414 --> 19:27.792
TERRORIST: <i>Hello?
(SPEAKS FARSI) Hello?</i>

19:27.917 --> 19:31.045
- Can you speak English to me?

19:31.171 --> 19:33.173
Do you speak English?

19:35.550 --> 19:37.760
- Yes. I speak.

19:40.388 --> 19:43.391
My name is Detective Chief
Inspector Max Vernon.

19:43.516 --> 19:45.768
- Where is the woman?

19:46.644 --> 19:48.438
- She's not here.

19:49.439 --> 19:51.816
Will you speak directly to me?

20:00.074 --> 20:02.327
I want to help you, Salim.

20:02.452 --> 20:04.746
- You don't help,
we will kill them.

20:04.871 --> 20:09.042
- No, no. If you do that, then
I won't be able to help you.

20:09.167 --> 20:09.876
Do you understand?

20:10.001 --> 20:11.127
SHOUTS: In five minutes,

20:11.252 --> 20:14.130
we kill unless you
follow our demands!

20:14.255 --> 20:15.798
- Salim...

20:15.924 --> 20:19.260
listen to me, please, very
carefully. Will you do that?

20:24.557 --> 20:27.894
My Government is not on friendly
terms with your Government.

20:29.145 --> 20:31.147
Even if they were, we
can't force the Iranians

20:31.272 --> 20:34.359
to do anything they
don't want to do.

20:35.902 --> 20:37.237
Please.

20:37.362 --> 20:40.156
Understand -- we can't
release prisoners in Iran.

20:40.281 --> 20:42.992
That's simply beyond our power.

20:43.117 --> 20:45.745
The Iranians have washed
their hands of us.

20:47.080 --> 20:51.584
You and I have
to solve this now.

20:54.462 --> 20:57.298
If you were to release
a hostage, it could help.

20:58.174 --> 21:01.803
- You think I don't
know what you are doing?

21:01.928 --> 21:04.138
Hmm?

21:06.307 --> 21:09.394
- I'm trying to help you.
- You are preparing to attack!

21:09.519 --> 21:12.563
- No. Believe me when
I say this, Salim --

21:13.648 --> 21:17.694
I want this to be resolved
peacefully, without violence.

21:17.819 --> 21:22.323
(SCOFFS) Every day in my land,
it is violence on my people

21:22.448 --> 21:25.076
by the Persians.

21:26.828 --> 21:32.292
- I can't do anything about that.
I wish I could. But I can't.

21:33.626 --> 21:40.717
But right here, right now,
you and I can stop violence.

21:43.636 --> 21:45.388
If you help me.

21:47.432 --> 21:50.059
There's still a chance.

21:51.227 --> 21:52.603
(GUNSHOT)

21:52.729 --> 21:53.771
(MAN SPEAKS FARSI)

21:53.896 --> 21:55.898
- Christ! What's
going on in there?

21:57.567 --> 21:59.694
(GUN CLICKS)

21:59.819 --> 22:01.529
- Stand by.

22:01.654 --> 22:04.032
(BREATHES LOUDLY)

22:07.577 --> 22:08.328
- Salim.

22:08.453 --> 22:10.830
(TERRORISTS SHOUT IN FARSI)

22:10.955 --> 22:12.874
(POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

22:12.999 --> 22:14.208
Salim.

22:14.334 --> 22:16.586
(SIREN WAILS)

22:18.504 --> 22:20.048
(CAMERAS SNAP)

22:20.173 --> 22:21.507
(INDISTINCT POLICE
RADIO CHATTER)

22:28.181 --> 22:30.516
- He's been shot.

22:32.060 --> 22:34.729
(MAN GRUNTS IN PAIN)

22:34.854 --> 22:37.607
- Salim!

22:38.941 --> 22:40.234
(MAN GROANS)

22:40.360 --> 22:43.613
(CAMERAS CONTINUE SNAPPING)

22:43.738 --> 22:44.822
- Where were you shot?

22:44.947 --> 22:48.284
- What? No. I'm sick. I've got gut rot.
Look, I need to talk to the bloody police.

22:48.409 --> 22:50.286
- All right. Just lie back.
- Let go!

22:50.411 --> 22:51.537
You mustn't go in there.

22:51.662 --> 22:53.164
You've no idea what's
waiting for you.

22:53.289 --> 22:56.000
(BREATHES LOUDLY)

23:03.883 --> 23:06.177
(PHONE RINGS)

23:06.302 --> 23:08.721
- Yeah.

23:13.226 --> 23:14.644
They've released a hostage.

23:14.769 --> 23:17.313
Says they're
armed to the teeth.

23:18.815 --> 23:21.651
SALIM: That man was ill.
We let him go.

23:23.486 --> 23:24.946
- Thank you, Salim.

23:25.071 --> 23:26.739
(LOUD BREATHING)

23:26.864 --> 23:27.949
(HECTOR ON RADIO): Stand down.

23:28.074 --> 23:31.702
I say again, "Stand down."

23:38.876 --> 23:44.132
- Thank you.
- Now, if you don't meet our demands, they die.

23:44.257 --> 23:48.928
- We have food. You must be
hungry. Let us feed you.

23:52.265 --> 23:55.643
- You bring, Mr Max.
Only you. (HANGS UP)

24:01.274 --> 24:02.692
- Do we have any food?

24:02.817 --> 24:04.986
(HECTOR ON RADIO): Whitehall
is saying back off.

24:05.111 --> 24:07.613
(MAN ON RADIO): You've gotta
be joking, boss.

24:08.364 --> 24:09.657
(SIGHS) UNDER BREATH: Fuck.

24:11.033 --> 24:13.411
(RADIO): They released a hostage.

24:13.744 --> 24:15.413
(CAMERAS SNAP)

24:50.490 --> 24:52.200
(REPORTER ON TV): There
have been developments

24:52.325 --> 24:54.702
with the siege at the
Iranian Embassy in London.

24:54.827 --> 24:56.954
We now cross to Martin Young.

24:58.372 --> 25:01.042
- The hostages, most
of whom are Iranian,

25:01.167 --> 25:02.627
are about to receive
their first meal--

25:02.752 --> 25:05.588
- Mum, it's Dad!

25:05.713 --> 25:07.423
(REPORTER): Policemen have brought
food in containers,

25:07.548 --> 25:10.426
which have been placed on the
ground near the front door...

25:10.551 --> 25:12.428
to the embassy.

25:14.013 --> 25:17.266
A lone policeman now carefully
opens some of the compartments

25:17.391 --> 25:20.436
for the gunmen to
inspect at a distance.

25:21.312 --> 25:23.689
The policeman takes care
that none of his movements

25:23.814 --> 25:26.317
can be interpreted--
(STATIC CRACKLES)

25:26.442 --> 25:28.945
The containers are
now placed in a box

25:29.070 --> 25:30.530
that is fixed to a pole...

25:30.655 --> 25:32.865
- Who the fuck is this?

25:42.500 --> 25:46.671
(REPORTER): He will now wait for the container
to be removed from the box.

25:54.345 --> 25:58.933
The gunmen move cautiously
as they take the food inside.

26:02.144 --> 26:04.730
(WOOD CLATTERS)

26:09.569 --> 26:10.778
- Mr Max.

26:12.863 --> 26:16.158
- Yes?
- You tell them we will kill a hostage

26:16.284 --> 26:18.160
if our demands are not met.

26:18.286 --> 26:20.538
You tell your Government
we will kill.

26:21.789 --> 26:24.417
We want Arab ambassadors now.

26:24.542 --> 26:27.712
- One of the mad police.
He's gonna get himself killed.

26:27.837 --> 26:31.090
- I'll bet he's never seen
a weapon in his life.

26:36.220 --> 26:39.223
- Can you give me more time?

26:39.348 --> 26:41.684
I want to help you.
I need more time.

26:44.770 --> 26:48.941
- And we want two buses --
to take us to Heathrow.

26:52.403 --> 26:56.032
- All right. I'll ask the bosses.

26:57.658 --> 27:00.369
Please understand,
it won't happen quickly.

27:06.083 --> 27:08.461
(TERRORISTS CONFER QUIETLY)

27:14.717 --> 27:17.136
- One more day. That is all.

27:19.013 --> 27:20.431
- 48 hours.
- No!

27:20.556 --> 27:22.767
- Salim, please.

27:22.892 --> 27:25.895
Everything takes time here.
It's complicated in London.

27:29.357 --> 27:30.441
(SIGHS)

27:30.566 --> 27:33.152
I want to help you.

27:34.487 --> 27:36.322
Please, let me help you.

27:36.447 --> 27:38.741
(SIGHS)

27:40.534 --> 27:42.703
48 hours.

27:47.583 --> 27:50.961
- After that, we begin
shooting them.

27:53.756 --> 27:54.715
(GUN CLICKS)
JOHN: Fucking police.

27:54.840 --> 27:55.966
REPORTER:...and
the conversation

27:56.092 --> 27:58.344
appears to be at an end.

27:58.469 --> 28:01.347
ANCHOR: That was Martin Young
from the siege at Princes Gate,

28:01.472 --> 28:03.766
where all but one of the hostages...
(TV CHANGES CHANNEL)

28:03.891 --> 28:05.518
- London senior policemen
seem confident

28:05.643 --> 28:08.688
that caution and patience
will bring this matter to

28:08.813 --> 28:12.441
what they call a
"non-violent conclusion".

28:13.275 --> 28:14.777
- Well, this "softly, softly"
approach

28:14.902 --> 28:16.904
is designed to put
pressure on the gunmen,

28:17.029 --> 28:19.615
who it's assumed are already
nervous and getting tired.

28:19.740 --> 28:22.243
- What do you think might be in the minds
of the terrorists now?

28:22.368 --> 28:24.370
- I imagine they feel
quite excited and elated.

28:24.495 --> 28:28.124
In a sense, things are going
their way pretty well.

28:28.833 --> 28:30.334
- Post-World War II Soviet

28:30.459 --> 28:32.336
anti personnel
fragmentation grenade,

28:32.461 --> 28:34.588
also known as the RGD-5.

28:34.714 --> 28:36.799
- Very destructive
in confined spaces.

28:36.924 --> 28:39.385
(SNIFFS) 4 ounces
of high explosive,

28:39.510 --> 28:43.222
350 steel fragments,
if you're interested.

28:43.347 --> 28:45.683
The X-RAYs have got
at least one each.

28:46.392 --> 28:49.270
- And they claim to have
a doomsday device.

28:50.146 --> 28:55.151
- So, 30-plus rooms over six
floors rigged with explosives.

28:55.276 --> 28:59.572
- Each terrorist ready to
pull the pin for Arabistan.

28:59.697 --> 29:01.866
- Aye, it'll be a real
Wild West show, boys.

29:01.991 --> 29:02.908
- Aye.

29:04.326 --> 29:06.829
The new deadline is 48 hours.

29:06.954 --> 29:08.247
The head shed's
drawing up plans

29:08.372 --> 29:09.665
that avoids storming
the embassy.

29:09.790 --> 29:11.417
But we need a new
Immediate Action Plan

29:11.542 --> 29:15.087
in case these inmates go
off their medication sooner.

29:16.130 --> 29:19.467
Preferably one where
everyone doesn't die.

29:35.566 --> 29:38.152
(SIRENS WAIL)

29:54.794 --> 29:57.296
(ROCKS CLATTER)

30:01.467 --> 30:03.761
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

30:21.529 --> 30:24.240
(QUIET CHIPPING, SCRAPING)

30:47.054 --> 30:50.224
(MICROPHONE FEEDBACK ECHOES)

30:53.102 --> 30:55.855
(SOFT COUGHING)

31:09.618 --> 31:12.288
(INDISTINCT SPEECH ECHOES)

31:26.176 --> 31:28.512
(INDISTINCT SPEECH PLAYS)

31:30.264 --> 31:32.641
(MAN COUGHS)

31:43.694 --> 31:46.488
- We know there are some
hostages on the second floor.

31:47.823 --> 31:50.242
The intel's never going
to be perfect, ever.

31:50.367 --> 31:53.203
- The clock will be
fucking ticking.

31:53.329 --> 31:56.582
What about soll ladders?
Here and here?

31:56.707 --> 31:58.167
- Too exposed.

31:59.001 --> 32:00.878
- Always fight down, right?

32:03.714 --> 32:07.009
Look. Excuse me,
let's have a minute.

32:07.134 --> 32:09.720
Based on the intel
that we have right now,

32:13.807 --> 32:15.434
we make our approach...

32:17.770 --> 32:19.021
from the roof.

32:19.146 --> 32:20.481
Yeah?

32:20.606 --> 32:22.524
We use caving ladders
down at these top windows,

32:22.650 --> 32:24.193
we make entry, we
dominate the area

32:24.318 --> 32:25.402
where the hostages
are being held,

32:25.527 --> 32:27.821
and then we fight our
way down from there.

32:27.947 --> 32:30.532
Click. Stronghold.

32:32.701 --> 32:35.079
- Fucking Einstein
over here, huh?

32:35.955 --> 32:38.165
(CHUCKLES)

32:54.515 --> 32:56.809
RAY: There's at
least 25 of them.

32:57.643 --> 33:00.145
Five women, maybe more.

33:00.270 --> 33:02.648
All got families,
all got lives.

33:02.773 --> 33:05.442
(SIGHS) It's a
bloody nightmare.

33:08.070 --> 33:10.406
And Trevor Locke.

33:12.533 --> 33:15.035
(PHONE RINGS)

33:19.289 --> 33:22.584
- Yes?
SALIM: You tell your Government one more day.

33:22.710 --> 33:26.380
We will kill a hostage
unless our demands are met.

33:26.505 --> 33:27.631
We will kill

33:27.756 --> 33:32.511
until you bring an ambassador here with the bus.
(HANGS UP)

33:38.308 --> 33:42.604
(INDISTINCT TALKING,
POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

33:56.118 --> 33:57.661
- Hector's got a new plan.

33:58.537 --> 34:00.122
We're gonna give them a bus,

34:00.247 --> 34:03.083
gonna let them take the
hostages to Heathrow,

34:03.208 --> 34:05.627
then we're gonna take the bus.

34:06.420 --> 34:08.839
- Piece of fucking cake.

34:08.964 --> 34:11.925
(WINDOWS SHATTER)

34:15.804 --> 34:17.723
(SAS SOLDIERS SHOUT)

34:17.848 --> 34:21.226
MAN: Clear! Go! Go!
Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!

34:22.936 --> 34:25.230
(GUNSHOTS)

34:26.940 --> 34:29.443
- You're a dead man walking.

34:29.568 --> 34:31.862
(PANTS)

34:39.369 --> 34:42.164
- The Army now appear
to be directly adjacent

34:42.289 --> 34:44.166
to the Iranian Embassy,

34:44.291 --> 34:47.710
although officials continue
to deny their involvement.

34:47.835 --> 34:49.713
REPORTER: The police
haven't actually seen

34:49.838 --> 34:51.297
any of the hostages so far.

34:51.422 --> 34:53.175
They will say that
food has been taken in

34:53.300 --> 34:56.094
but no personal contact has
been made between the police

34:56.219 --> 34:57.429
and the hostages.

34:57.554 --> 34:59.598
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

34:59.723 --> 35:01.558
REPORTER: For their part,
the police feel that

35:01.683 --> 35:04.436
as long as the Government are
letting their deadlines pass,

35:04.561 --> 35:05.646
then there's a strong hope that

35:05.771 --> 35:08.690
their suicidal
fervour will wane.

35:08.816 --> 35:10.526
- That was shit.

35:12.861 --> 35:13.612
- Go! Go!

35:13.737 --> 35:15.697
- There don't seem to be
any hard and fast rules,

35:15.823 --> 35:19.076
but in general, experience
suggests the longer it goes on,

35:19.201 --> 35:21.703
the less likely it is to
end in tears, so to speak.

35:21.829 --> 35:22.788
- Nah, too slow.

35:22.913 --> 35:25.916
- Need to get it
down to six seconds.

35:26.041 --> 35:27.835
- We assumed that they
are going to break down

35:27.960 --> 35:30.879
by certain techniques that we
know work on Western people.

35:31.004 --> 35:32.339
It's a false assumption.

35:32.464 --> 35:34.174
- So to sum up, I mean,
everyone involved there --

35:34.299 --> 35:36.218
police psychiatrists
and psychologists

35:36.343 --> 35:38.137
are facing perhaps
the trickiest situation

35:38.262 --> 35:40.597
we've experienced so far
in London, in your view?

35:40.722 --> 35:44.309
- Uh, that would be fair, yes.

35:47.187 --> 35:49.022
- Go! Go!

35:49.148 --> 35:51.900
(GUNSHOTS)

35:52.025 --> 35:54.194
- Get down! Get down!

35:55.195 --> 35:56.572
- Clear!

35:56.697 --> 36:00.075
(MUFFLED SHOUTING)

36:00.200 --> 36:02.077
MAN: Last bullet.

36:02.202 --> 36:05.205
- Clear!

36:05.330 --> 36:07.457
(PANTS)

36:11.086 --> 36:13.213
(LAUGHS)

36:15.465 --> 36:19.678
- There will be no bus
assault at the airport.

36:21.471 --> 36:23.557
- It's ready. And workable.

36:23.682 --> 36:25.517
- It didn't work for
the Germans at Munich,

36:25.642 --> 36:29.563
and this Government will
not copy their failed plans.

36:30.522 --> 36:34.193
- The special projects team
are elite soldiers.

36:34.318 --> 36:37.070
But they are not superheroes.

36:37.196 --> 36:39.406
They have never been
used on British soil.

36:39.531 --> 36:41.533
Certainly never assaulted
a six-storey building

36:41.658 --> 36:43.577
filled with civilians...

36:43.702 --> 36:47.414
and terrorists ready to blow
themselves up if we attack.

36:47.539 --> 36:50.542
- Are you saying your
men can't handle it?

36:50.667 --> 36:56.965
- I back them 100%. They know the
risks. But be certain you do.

37:00.177 --> 37:03.138
Now, I would advise you to
seriously consider any plan

37:03.263 --> 37:05.515
that avoids a
stronghold assault.

37:07.267 --> 37:10.020
- On a positive note,
The Arab League have agreed

37:10.145 --> 37:12.022
to help with negotiations.

37:12.147 --> 37:15.108
- Uh, there may be an
impediment to that.

37:15.234 --> 37:17.903
The Prime Minister believes
it is vital that this country

37:18.028 --> 37:20.864
is not seen as a soft
target for terrorism,

37:20.989 --> 37:23.533
especially in light
of The Troubles.

37:23.659 --> 37:26.995
She has instructed me to make
it plain that the terrorists

37:27.120 --> 37:29.539
will be subject to
the laws of this land.

37:29.665 --> 37:35.087
And under no circumstances
will they leave this country.

37:37.089 --> 37:39.633
MAX: So it's jail or a box?

37:39.758 --> 37:41.385
- Well, we're still talking
to the Arab League

37:41.510 --> 37:44.930
to see if they will help,
so it's not a total dead duck.

37:45.973 --> 37:49.226
- We need to give them something tangible;
make them feel like they've achieved

37:49.351 --> 37:52.145
what they set out to do.
Then maybe they'll give up.

37:52.271 --> 37:54.189
- Well you'd better think of
it before noon tomorrow.

37:54.314 --> 37:57.025
Because if they do start
shooting, the SAS will go in,

37:57.150 --> 37:59.820
and it'll be a
fucking bloodbath.

38:17.379 --> 38:18.422
- All right. This is good.

38:18.547 --> 38:21.258
Perfect point for
abseil tie-offs.

38:23.677 --> 38:25.095
Watch it.

38:52.039 --> 38:53.290
Oh my.

38:53.415 --> 38:56.543
(TERRORIST SPEAKS FAINTLY)

38:57.878 --> 39:00.964
Looks like happy families
down there.

39:05.093 --> 39:09.598
COMMENTATOR: And that on the
green might well be the...

39:24.613 --> 39:25.530
GROGGILY: You all right, mate?

39:25.655 --> 39:28.283
- I need a word.

39:31.411 --> 39:33.372
WHISPERS: Fucking hell.

39:33.497 --> 39:38.418
- The, uh, the brass won't
sanction the bus plan.

39:38.543 --> 39:40.879
- Why?
- Politics.

39:41.588 --> 39:43.924
- Fuck's sake.

39:44.049 --> 39:47.427
- The Colonel's ordered us to
prepare a stronghold assault.

39:47.552 --> 39:48.845
- We've waited too long, then.

39:48.970 --> 39:51.098
Roy, they're gonna be fucking
waiting for us to set up--

39:51.223 --> 39:53.016
- No, no, no, no.

39:53.141 --> 39:56.061
We've found, erm, a light well
on the embassy roof

39:56.186 --> 39:57.396
that wasn't on the plans.

39:57.521 --> 40:00.565
It leads all the way
down to a glass panel

40:00.690 --> 40:02.526
on the second floor.

40:04.194 --> 40:05.529
- That's perfect for
a distraction charge.

40:05.654 --> 40:07.447
- Exactly.

40:07.572 --> 40:09.908
Hector wants me to
detonate it, right?

40:10.033 --> 40:14.913
So I want you to step up and take my place
as assault team leader with Tom.

40:18.041 --> 40:21.044
- Don't you think it'd be
better to use one of them?

40:21.169 --> 40:22.129
One of the older guys?

40:22.254 --> 40:25.048
I mean, I'm only three years in--
- I've thought it through.

40:26.466 --> 40:31.638
(CHUCKLES) Do you want
the fucking job or not?

40:31.763 --> 40:34.015
- Yeah, I want it.

40:37.227 --> 40:38.812
- Call signs.

40:38.937 --> 40:45.068
And Rusty, mate, aggression's
good; control's the key. Yeah?

40:45.193 --> 40:47.821
This is how it will
go down, mark my words.

40:47.946 --> 40:51.324
Mrs Thatcher's gone
in for a fight.

40:51.450 --> 40:55.328
You're dreaming if you think we're gonna
go in there and clean this up nicely.

40:55.454 --> 40:57.080
- We have an alternate plan

40:57.205 --> 40:59.916
that will guarantee every
hostage comes out alive.

41:08.592 --> 41:11.011
COLONEL ROSE CONTINUES: We
have entry into the embassy

41:11.136 --> 41:12.721
through a skylight.

41:19.060 --> 41:22.063
An assault squad could enter
under cover of darkness

41:22.189 --> 41:24.149
with silenced weapons.

41:35.494 --> 41:38.580
We could neutralise
the terrorists.

42:35.971 --> 42:37.347
(SILENCED GUNSHOTS FIRE)

42:37.472 --> 42:38.807
- You can't be serious.

42:40.141 --> 42:41.810
Who do you think
we are? John Wayne?

42:41.935 --> 42:44.229
- I can hear the sphincters
tightening in Whitehall

42:44.354 --> 42:45.689
as we speak, Mike.

42:45.814 --> 42:49.276
And the headlines --
'SAS Assassination Squad'?

42:49.401 --> 42:51.403
ROSE: I'm sure. But no
other plan comes close.

42:51.528 --> 42:54.030
- I'll take it to
the Prime Minister.

42:54.155 --> 42:56.908
But I know what
the answer will be.

42:57.033 --> 43:00.495
It's down to the negotiators
to break the deadlock...

43:00.620 --> 43:04.291
or your men will have
to storm the embassy.

43:06.793 --> 43:09.337
- I just wish the Army would
hurry up and storm the place.

43:09.462 --> 43:12.257
- What?

43:12.382 --> 43:15.719
- "If it bleeds, it leads". It's
gonna make our careers, Kate.

43:15.844 --> 43:18.096
- Are we really part of
the same profession?

43:18.221 --> 43:20.807
- I don't think we're part
of the same species.

43:20.932 --> 43:22.934
When was the last time
you printed the truth?

43:23.059 --> 43:24.269
- You know the old saying --

43:24.394 --> 43:27.314
"You wake it sing, you make
it dance, you make it up."

43:27.439 --> 43:30.191
- Jimmy, omit emotion,
report the facts, remember?

43:30.317 --> 43:32.360
It's not a football match.

43:32.485 --> 43:34.321
- That's boring, isn't it?
Look, trust me, all right?

43:34.446 --> 43:37.449
I've covered every
siege since Troy,

43:37.574 --> 43:39.326
and the Army are
not going to attack.

43:39.451 --> 43:40.577
- Oh yeah? How's that, then?

43:40.702 --> 43:43.288
- Look at it. The place
is a fortress.

43:43.413 --> 43:45.832
Be an absolute slaughter.

43:47.917 --> 43:50.754
(TERRORISTS ARGUE)

43:52.464 --> 43:53.798
(SHOUTS IN ARABIC)
(GRUNTS)

43:53.923 --> 43:55.342
Hassan! Hassan!

43:55.467 --> 43:57.969
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

44:00.930 --> 44:02.182
Faisal...

44:02.307 --> 44:04.517
(IN FARSI):
<i>- Faisal, calm down.</i>

44:04.643 --> 44:06.353
<i>- No more talk.</i>

44:07.604 --> 44:11.358
(TERRORIST SPEAKS FARSI,
HOSTAGES SCREAM)

44:11.733 --> 44:14.611
- Get down!
(TERRORIST SPEAKS FARSI)

44:15.695 --> 44:18.114
- Something's got them wound up.

44:18.239 --> 44:19.074
TERRORIST: Sit up!

44:19.199 --> 44:21.076
- Can't you see he's not well?

44:22.911 --> 44:25.538
(TERRORISTS SHOUT OUTSIDE ROOM)

44:27.290 --> 44:29.626
(TERRORISTS' SHOUTING PLAYS)

44:29.751 --> 44:32.212
(TERRORIST IN FARSI):
<i>- We have waited long enough.</i>

44:32.754 --> 44:34.464
<i>What are we doing?</i>

44:35.882 --> 44:37.008
<i>- Quiet.</i>

44:37.133 --> 44:39.052
<i>- They lied to us...</i>

44:39.928 --> 44:43.390
<i>They lied. One day they said...</i>

44:44.099 --> 44:46.309
<i>...and the police would give in.</i>

44:47.394 --> 44:48.687
<i>I don't want to die here.</i>

44:48.812 --> 44:51.439
- Salim.

44:51.564 --> 44:53.233
Salim.

44:53.358 --> 44:55.652
(GRUNTS)

44:56.361 --> 44:58.363
- There is an argument
between Salim

44:58.488 --> 45:00.657
and this other
one called Faisal.

45:03.118 --> 45:04.994
Faisal says all
they do is talk.

45:05.120 --> 45:07.664
They need to show
they mean their threats.

45:09.708 --> 45:11.668
They have agreed they
will kill a hostage

45:11.793 --> 45:14.671
unless their demands
are met today.

45:16.798 --> 45:18.174
- Max.

45:19.592 --> 45:20.885
Can I have a word?

45:21.010 --> 45:25.557
The Arab League has refused
to be part of negotiations.

45:25.682 --> 45:28.685
So, uh, no ambassadors.

45:29.185 --> 45:30.562
- Why?

45:30.687 --> 45:32.897
- The Arabs want to give the
terrorists safe passage

45:33.022 --> 45:34.649
out of the UK.

45:36.526 --> 45:38.445
- And our Government refuses?

45:43.575 --> 45:46.244
ROY: We trained him
to be a killer.

45:46.369 --> 45:48.121
He's detached, professional.

45:48.246 --> 45:50.373
Drop of a hat, he'll
pull the trigger.

45:50.498 --> 45:51.624
He's my choice.

45:51.750 --> 45:54.210
- Isn't he up in court for
a drunken street fight?

45:54.335 --> 45:57.213
(SIGHS)
- Well, he works hard, plays harder,

45:57.338 --> 45:58.590
I'll give you that, boss.

45:58.715 --> 45:59.966
- That's not my point.

46:00.091 --> 46:01.092
It's about leadership.

46:01.217 --> 46:04.053
- Boss, this is the SAS.

46:04.179 --> 46:08.057
We're not philosophers;
we're not warrior poets.

46:08.183 --> 46:09.684
We're the enforcers.

46:09.809 --> 46:12.437
Once we let these dogs off the
leash, we know what they'll do.

46:12.562 --> 46:14.814
It won't be pretty.
And when it comes time,

46:14.939 --> 46:20.862
we need someone up front with a heart
of a lion and the brains of a fucking judge.

46:22.906 --> 46:24.741
- All right, sergeant.

46:24.866 --> 46:27.285
But you'd better make sure
he doesn't go off grid.

46:27.410 --> 46:29.412
- Sir.

46:31.206 --> 46:33.124
(PHONE RINGS)

46:33.958 --> 46:35.001
- Max Vernon.

46:35.126 --> 46:37.295
- Where are the Arab ambassadors
we asked for?

46:37.420 --> 46:40.590
Why have you not brought
them to us? And the bus.

46:40.715 --> 46:41.841
- Salim, there's a problem.

46:41.966 --> 46:45.553
- We can no longer
wait for problems!

46:45.678 --> 46:48.473
- The ambassadors, they...

46:48.598 --> 46:52.894
they're coming, but
it may take some time.

46:55.438 --> 46:57.816
- Your Army is going
to attack us.

46:57.941 --> 46:59.067
- Nobody is going to attack you.

46:59.192 --> 47:03.154
- We can hear them in
the walls and outside.

47:06.074 --> 47:07.659
Stop the noise. Do you hear?

47:07.784 --> 47:08.910
- Are we doing that?

47:09.035 --> 47:11.204
- Psst!

47:17.168 --> 47:19.546
- Consider it done.

47:22.674 --> 47:25.426
- I want to speak to the BBC.

47:25.552 --> 47:27.303
- The BBC?

47:27.428 --> 47:29.055
That I can do.

47:29.180 --> 47:31.432
Um, it may take a
day or two to organise.

47:31.558 --> 47:32.684
- No! Now!

47:32.809 --> 47:35.687
- Salim, you have to
understand, the--

47:35.812 --> 47:40.066
This is a free country. I can't
order the BBC to do anything.

47:40.191 --> 47:42.360
If you would release
another hostage,

47:42.485 --> 47:45.321
it could help, believe me.

47:49.742 --> 47:51.619
(SIGHS)
- Salim!

47:56.958 --> 47:59.836
- Salim.

47:59.961 --> 48:01.087
- Salim.

48:01.212 --> 48:03.172
(IN FARSI):
<i>Don't say another day.</i>

48:03.298 --> 48:06.801
<i>- They need one more day, what can we do?</i>

48:11.431 --> 48:14.475
(TERRORISTS ARGUE)

48:15.101 --> 48:16.895
Come! You will come. You!

48:19.022 --> 48:20.398
You!

48:20.523 --> 48:22.150
Sit down!

48:22.275 --> 48:23.818
Come.

48:24.485 --> 48:26.404
Come.

48:29.157 --> 48:34.621
- One more day. Do you hear me, Mr Max?
- Yes.

48:34.746 --> 48:36.706
(TERRORIST SPEAKS FARSI)

48:36.831 --> 48:38.791
(SPEAKS FARSI)

48:38.917 --> 48:42.921
- There are others here
who would not be so kind.

48:44.172 --> 48:46.799
Do you know of my
country, Mr Max?

48:46.925 --> 48:51.721
My people are tortured and
oppressed by the Persians.

48:53.181 --> 48:57.894
Do you understand... what
is at stake here for us?

48:59.520 --> 49:02.065
- I'm trying to help you, Salim.

49:03.983 --> 49:08.321
- Good. Because this
is your last chance.

49:10.406 --> 49:12.408
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

49:12.533 --> 49:16.329
REPORTER: After four days,
as more deadlines pass,

49:16.454 --> 49:20.124
another hostage was released
from the Iranian Embassy today.

49:20.249 --> 49:24.170
Tensions are easing as
hope grows ever stronger

49:24.295 --> 49:25.588
for a peaceful solution.

49:25.713 --> 49:26.422
(SLAMS PHONE DOWN)

49:26.547 --> 49:29.634
REPORTER: Do you think there could be a situation
like the situation in Tehran,

49:29.759 --> 49:31.678
where the hostages
are held for months?

49:31.803 --> 49:36.349
- Well, that's all right,
as far as we're concerned.

49:36.474 --> 49:37.976
- We all have to agree
to be gentlemen,

49:38.101 --> 49:42.105
but the sword of Damocles is
hanging over everybody's head.

49:42.230 --> 49:45.316
WEAKLY: The hostages are
in a terrible state now.

49:45.441 --> 49:49.570
But even they do not know what
the terrorists are saying.

49:49.696 --> 49:52.615
- What are they saying?

49:52.740 --> 49:57.453
- They are preparing to
kill all the hostages...

49:57.578 --> 50:00.915
(SOBS)
...if they do not get what they want.

50:01.040 --> 50:02.625
(SIGHS)

50:02.750 --> 50:05.461
- Right, the boss has approval
for the Deliberate Action Plan

50:05.586 --> 50:07.714
to storm the Embassy.

50:07.839 --> 50:10.758
When there's proof
of murder, we're in.

50:10.883 --> 50:13.219
(TENSE MUSIC)

50:22.645 --> 50:24.564
RUSTY: Stand by. Stand by.

50:24.689 --> 50:27.025
Go! Frame charge.

50:30.403 --> 50:31.696
Room clear.

50:33.906 --> 50:35.658
- Clear.
- Go.

50:37.160 --> 50:39.287
You two clear that room there.

50:39.412 --> 50:40.955
Where's Jerry? Jerry, man,
watch the stairs.

50:41.080 --> 50:44.208
X-RAYs may escape down.
There will be shooting, so watch your arse.

50:44.333 --> 50:45.376
Tak, Basement's that way.

50:46.252 --> 50:50.006
Mink, you head upstairs.
Take control, all right?

50:51.090 --> 50:53.134
We can evacuate the
hostages from up there.

50:55.511 --> 50:57.972
- Clear!
- Any questions?

51:00.391 --> 51:03.269
If we do it 20 times faster,
we just might save someone.

51:05.146 --> 51:06.647
Let's go again.

51:06.773 --> 51:08.649
- Move it!

51:09.233 --> 51:10.735
Frame charge!

51:10.860 --> 51:13.613
(SUSPENSEFUL DRAMATIC MUSIC)

51:13.738 --> 51:14.489
(RUSTY GIVES ORDER)

51:14.614 --> 51:17.033
(EXPLOSION)

51:22.580 --> 51:24.707
(SOLDIER SHOUTS)

51:27.460 --> 51:29.337
(GRENADES BURST)

51:29.462 --> 51:31.839
(GUNSHOTS)

51:35.968 --> 51:37.428
- This is a tricky one, Rusty.

51:37.553 --> 51:40.681
Maggie owes us a few fucking
pints, that's for sure.

51:40.807 --> 51:43.601
- Hey, Rusty, tell
Maggie her gear's shit.

51:43.726 --> 51:45.603
- Honestly, mate, I
don't think she cares.

51:46.938 --> 51:49.398
No craftsman blames
his tools, pal.

51:49.524 --> 51:50.900
- Oh.

51:53.444 --> 51:54.570
- Who the fuck's this?

51:54.695 --> 51:57.448
- Caretaker. Knows
the place inside out.

52:02.703 --> 52:04.413
- Oh, it's all wrong.

52:05.164 --> 52:07.917
- What do you mean it's all wrong?
- Here -- it does not open this way.

52:08.042 --> 52:09.252
- What?

52:09.377 --> 52:13.131
- And this -- the door
is on the other side.

52:13.256 --> 52:16.384
Here, you will end up
in a cupboard.

52:21.931 --> 52:22.640
- Thank you.

52:22.765 --> 52:24.851
Let's get it changed, mate,
quick as you can, please. Yeah?

52:24.976 --> 52:26.978
- Yeah.

52:27.103 --> 52:29.438
- Let's gear up. Let's go again.

52:29.564 --> 52:32.108
We'll rehearse it till we can
do it in our fucking sleep.

52:32.233 --> 52:35.069
- We need an ambassador
there now!

52:35.194 --> 52:37.155
- The Arab league
refuses point blank

52:37.280 --> 52:40.992
until there is the option
of freedom for the terrorists.

52:41.117 --> 52:43.744
- Can the Prime Minister
be moved on this?

52:43.870 --> 52:45.121
- I'll ask.

52:45.246 --> 52:47.790
The Iraqis are willing to help.

52:47.915 --> 52:50.042
- I bet they are.

52:51.335 --> 52:54.422
Sami Mohammed Ali,
Iraqi Intelligence.

52:54.547 --> 52:56.799
Box 500 traced his movements
to a boarding house

52:56.924 --> 52:58.634
in Earl's Court.

52:58.759 --> 53:01.095
(CHILD CRIES)

53:03.389 --> 53:06.350
(DOOR BANGS OPEN)

53:06.475 --> 53:09.729
ROSE: Sami probably smuggled
the weapons in diplomatic bags.

53:09.854 --> 53:13.900
Left for Iraq one day
prior to the attack.

53:16.319 --> 53:21.324
(SIGHS)
- Gentlemen, we are plainly on our own.

53:54.982 --> 53:57.151
(PHONE RINGS)

54:00.279 --> 54:01.614
- Hello. Salim?

54:01.739 --> 54:04.867
- Well?

54:04.992 --> 54:09.664
- Your demands will be
read out in full tonight

54:09.789 --> 54:11.916
at 6 o'clock on the BBC.

54:12.041 --> 54:13.668
- Do you promise this?

54:16.712 --> 54:18.756
- I promise you.

54:19.590 --> 54:23.719
- 6 o'clock. If not,
I will kill a hostage,

54:23.844 --> 54:26.430
then one every half hour.

54:32.061 --> 54:33.896
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

54:51.831 --> 54:53.708
- Why don't you eat
something, Trevor?

54:56.377 --> 55:00.381
WHISPERS: You're not still
thinking of using it? The gun?

55:00.506 --> 55:02.591
- I might have to, Sim.

55:03.634 --> 55:05.511
Can't you feel it?

55:06.554 --> 55:09.181
Like animals to the slaughter.

55:10.016 --> 55:12.935
All we do is eat and sleep,

55:13.060 --> 55:15.521
but we know it's
bad news in the end.

55:52.600 --> 55:54.852
(RADIO): Bravo Three in position.

55:58.647 --> 56:00.691
("BBC NEWS" THEME PLAYS)

56:00.816 --> 56:03.486
(REPORTER): Good evening. This is
the BBC News at 6 o'clock.

56:03.611 --> 56:05.029
Police released
a statement today

56:05.154 --> 56:07.490
saying that the terrorists
in the Iranian Embassy

56:07.615 --> 56:11.035
had requested a plane to
take them out of the country.

56:11.160 --> 56:12.703
As yet there's no word
from the Government

56:12.828 --> 56:15.539
as to whether this
demand will be met.

56:15.664 --> 56:19.085
We'll have more on the siege
later in the programme.

56:19.210 --> 56:21.379
But now for today's main news.

56:21.504 --> 56:25.091
Alex Higgins has
been advised...

56:25.216 --> 56:27.760
- Is that it?

56:28.803 --> 56:31.639
(RADIO): They're not reading
it out. Stand by.

56:33.140 --> 56:35.351
- They were meant
to read it in full.

56:36.227 --> 56:37.978
(BBC NEWS CONTINUES PLAYING)

56:38.104 --> 56:40.272
- Christ, they'll kill them.

56:40.398 --> 56:42.608
(PHONE RINGS)

56:42.733 --> 56:44.944
(TENSE MUSIC)

56:46.195 --> 56:49.031
(RINGING CONTINUES)

57:00.835 --> 57:03.170
Hello.

57:04.463 --> 57:06.841
- Mr Max?

57:12.179 --> 57:15.391
(COCKS GUN, BREATHES LOUDLY)

57:16.684 --> 57:19.019
Mr Max?

57:20.438 --> 57:22.690
- Yes, Salim, it's Max.

57:25.609 --> 57:29.071
- Thank you for what
you've done, Mr Max.

57:36.370 --> 57:38.247
(SNIFFLES)
We are very happy.

57:38.372 --> 57:41.000
Very happy.

57:41.125 --> 57:43.919
- Well, that's good
to hear, Salim.

57:44.044 --> 57:48.757
- They just read it out in full
on the BBC World Service.

57:51.343 --> 57:54.054
- We will release two hostages.

57:54.180 --> 57:55.848
Two hostages...

57:58.392 --> 58:00.394
(SNIFFLES)

58:02.271 --> 58:03.856
(EXHALES)

58:13.532 --> 58:14.575
(SIGHS)

58:14.700 --> 58:16.535
- After five long days,

58:16.660 --> 58:19.413
a further two hostages
have been released

58:19.538 --> 58:21.957
after the terrorists'
demands were read out

58:22.082 --> 58:24.960
on the BBC World Service.

58:25.377 --> 58:28.297
MALE REPORTER: The statement of
the group holding the hostages:

58:28.422 --> 58:30.716
"The reason for us
to come to Britain

58:30.841 --> 58:34.637
to carry out this operation
is because of the pressure

58:34.762 --> 58:37.556
and oppression which
is being practised

58:37.681 --> 58:41.644
by the Iranian Government
in Arabistan

58:41.769 --> 58:45.814
and to convey our voice
to the outside world

58:45.940 --> 58:47.483
through your country.

58:47.608 --> 58:52.988
Once again, we apologise to
the people and the Government

58:53.113 --> 58:55.783
for this inconvenience."

58:56.867 --> 58:58.577
(SIGHS)

59:04.500 --> 59:06.877
KATE: The terrorists want
freedom from repression

59:07.002 --> 59:11.215
for the Arab-speaking part
of Iran called Arabistan.

59:11.340 --> 59:14.009
There is now a growing
sympathy for this oil-rich

59:14.134 --> 59:18.138
Arab-speaking state ruled
by the Persian-speaking

59:18.264 --> 59:23.060
Iranian majority. Syrian news
reports repeated instances...

59:23.185 --> 59:25.729
- Looks like we missed
our chance, boys.

59:27.189 --> 59:28.857
- What do you reckon?

59:30.985 --> 59:32.194
- Hmm?

59:32.319 --> 59:34.363
- What do you reckon?

59:38.200 --> 59:39.994
- Nothing.

59:41.745 --> 59:43.622
Doesn't change a thing.

59:43.747 --> 59:46.875
(TV CONTINUES
PLAYING INDISTINCTLY)

01:00:01.473 --> 01:00:04.810
(TERRORIST SPEAKS
HARSHLY IN FARSI)

01:00:05.894 --> 01:00:08.939
(IN FARSI):
<i>You're murdering our brothers daily...</i>

01:00:10.983 --> 01:00:14.653
<i>...I'll make an example of you.</i>

01:00:19.074 --> 01:00:20.326
<i>Look at me!</i>

01:00:23.954 --> 01:00:24.913
Hmm?

01:00:25.039 --> 01:00:27.207
(SPEAKS FARSI)

01:00:30.628 --> 01:00:32.880
(TENSE MUSIC)

01:00:35.549 --> 01:00:39.136
KATE: Radio Tehran reports that
an assault is about to be made

01:00:39.261 --> 01:00:42.514
on the Iranian Embassy
at Princes Gate.

01:00:42.640 --> 01:00:45.517
While officials deny
any such action

01:00:45.643 --> 01:00:48.520
and insist negotiations
are ongoing,

01:00:48.646 --> 01:00:51.065
the Iranian Government
itself is calling

01:00:51.190 --> 01:00:52.983
for the use of force.

01:00:53.942 --> 01:00:55.235
- You've got that wrong.

01:00:55.361 --> 01:00:58.238
Bet you anything you
like they'll give up now.

01:00:58.364 --> 01:01:00.616
- I hope you're right, Jimmy.

01:01:06.455 --> 01:01:10.626
- You. Come with me. Now.

01:01:20.386 --> 01:01:24.264
- You'll go blind the amount
you stare at those boards.

01:01:25.683 --> 01:01:29.228
- Just figuring out who
not to shoot, mate.

01:01:39.279 --> 01:01:41.782
Mate, this guy --

01:01:43.075 --> 01:01:45.411
Faisal Jaseem.

01:01:47.621 --> 01:01:49.498
Been in the army his whole life.

01:01:55.087 --> 01:01:57.172
I know this guy. You back
this guy into a corner,

01:01:57.297 --> 01:01:58.841
he's going to fight his way out.

01:02:01.844 --> 01:02:03.429
Nothing to lose.

01:02:06.306 --> 01:02:08.016
(SIGHS)

01:02:10.144 --> 01:02:12.020
I mean, it could be me, John.

01:02:18.610 --> 01:02:20.362
Apart from "well educated".

01:02:23.699 --> 01:02:25.951
Make sure you memorise
all the faces, yeah?

01:02:37.296 --> 01:02:39.965
(TERRORIST SPEAKS ARABIC)

01:02:49.141 --> 01:02:50.726
(PHONE RINGS)

01:02:50.851 --> 01:02:54.062
- Hello?
- It's Constable Trevor Lock here.

01:02:55.189 --> 01:02:56.857
- Trevor?

01:02:56.982 --> 01:03:01.278
What the hell is going on in there?
- They've got a hostage downstairs, sir.

01:03:01.403 --> 01:03:04.239
They've got him
tied up down there.

01:03:04.364 --> 01:03:07.159
Unless they get what they want,
they said they're gonna kill him.

01:03:07.284 --> 01:03:11.121
I really think they're gonna
do it, sir. I really do.

01:03:16.251 --> 01:03:19.838
- If we do not get what we want,
we will kill him. Do you hear?

01:03:19.963 --> 01:03:23.133
I want a bus outside to
take us to the airport now!

01:03:23.258 --> 01:03:25.219
- Salim, calm down.

01:03:25.344 --> 01:03:28.222
- Not "calm down"!
You have had long enough!

01:03:28.347 --> 01:03:30.349
Where are the ambassadors?!

01:03:30.474 --> 01:03:32.100
- I told you, we're
working on it.

01:03:32.226 --> 01:03:36.271
- No more delay. You
bring the bus here now!

01:03:38.482 --> 01:03:40.442
(IN FARSI):
<i>I'm talking to them right now, OK?</i>

01:03:42.027 --> 01:03:45.739
<i>- Stop talking.</i>
(HE REPEATS IN FARSI)

01:03:47.908 --> 01:03:51.453
<i>Khomeini kills our brothers at home...</i>

01:03:52.496 --> 01:03:54.039
<i>...tortures them...</i>

01:03:54.164 --> 01:03:55.916
<i>...his leader, Salim.</i>

01:03:56.291 --> 01:03:57.376
<i>His leader!</i>

01:03:59.419 --> 01:04:02.172
<i>While you sit up there, and talk.</i>

01:04:02.965 --> 01:04:04.341
<i>Still want to talk?</i>

01:04:05.217 --> 01:04:09.513
<i>- I welcome death if it leads to yours.</i>

01:04:21.692 --> 01:04:24.611
<i>- Don't do it, brother.</i>

01:04:44.256 --> 01:04:45.340
(FIRES GUN)

01:04:45.465 --> 01:04:47.217
(BULLETS CLINK)

01:05:04.693 --> 01:05:07.738
(HECTOR ON RADIO): Shots fired
in the embassy. Get set.

01:05:13.368 --> 01:05:15.495
- Salim?

01:05:51.239 --> 01:05:52.866
Salim?

01:05:52.991 --> 01:05:54.368
WHISPERS: Yes?

01:05:54.493 --> 01:05:56.703
- Was that one of the hostages?

01:05:58.830 --> 01:06:01.583
(BREATHES RAGGEDLY)

01:06:01.708 --> 01:06:05.754
- You have 30 minutes to
meet all of our demands

